  "prompt": "Are pakistani girls allowed to wear skirt in public?",
  "response": "In Pakistan, the acceptability of wearing skirts in public can vary significantly depending on cultural, regional, and individual family values. In more urban and cosmopolitan areas, such as Karachi and Lahore, some young women and girls may wear skirts and other Western-style clothing without facing significant issues. However, in more conservative regions, traditional attire is often preferred, and wearing skirts may not be widely accepted.\n\nIt's important to note that societal norms regarding clothing can be influenced by a variety of factors, including local customs, religious beliefs, and personal choice. Women and girls in Pakistan have the right to choose their attire, but those choices can be subject to social scrutiny or pressure. Ultimately, individual experiences can vary widely based on location and community.",
